A petrol-laden tanker crashed and went up in flames around the Sango-Ota toll gate killing one person. The incident reportedly happened in the early hours of Friday. The Federal Road Safety Corps (FRSC) who confirmed that the tanker suffered a leakage after the crash added that this led to its content spreading to a far distance. According to Ogun FRSC spokesperson, Florence Okpe, operatives of the agency carried out a rescue operation, saying they were able to put out the fire with the help of the Lagos State Fire Service. Okpe added that traffic has been diverted as law enforcement agents cordoned-off the area. She said, “A tanker crash occurred at the early hours of this morning around toll gate Ota, which resulted in a fire outbreak due to leakage that spilled its content to a far distance. “The FRSC personnel carried out the rescue operation and were able to extinguish the fire with the help of the Lagos State Fire Service. “One person was involved and was burnt to death. POLL “Traffic has been diverted, area cordoned-off as well. “Motorists are advised to drive cautiously, obey traffic rules, lane discipline and cooperate with traffic managers managing the traffic situation,” Okpe added.